    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Expected Outcomes</h2>

            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">After completing this reset plan:</p>

            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Configuration Complexity Reduced:</strong> From 30+ files to 8-10 essential files in /.zencoder/rules/</li>
                <li><strong>Clear Authority:</strong> core.md is the single source of truth. All other files reference it.</li>
                <li><strong>Improved Compliance:</strong> Mandatory logging + clear rules should increase agent rule-following from 20% to 70-80%</li>
                <li><strong>Better Diagnostics:</strong> prompts_log.yaml will capture every agent action, making it easy to audit and identify violations</li>
                <li><strong>Non-Overlapping Roles:</strong> Each specialized agent (Cleanup, Docker, Main) has clear boundaries</li>
                <li><strong>Project Standard Integration:</strong> All agents reference consolidated YAML, ensuring consistency with project guidelines</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Testing &amp; Verification After Reset</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Test 1: Cleanup Agent - File Editing</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <strong>Command:</strong> Ask Cleanup Agent to edit a /.zencoder/rules/ file. <br/>
                <strong>Expected:</strong> Agent reads core.md first, uses ask_questions() function if needed, logs action to prompts_log.yaml with success=true.
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Test 2: Compliance Audit</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <strong>Query:</strong> Ask agent to summarize prompts_log.yaml entries from last 5 prompts. <br/>
                <strong>Expected:</strong> Agent reports which rules were followed, which were not, identifies patterns.
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Test 3: Role Boundary Enforcement</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <strong>Command:</strong> Ask Cleanup Agent to edit application code in Comserv/lib/. <br/>
                <strong>Expected:</strong> Agent refuses (boundary violation), explains why, suggests switching to MainAgent role.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div class="success" style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <h2 style="color: var(--success-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Next Steps</h2>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>Approval:</strong> User reviews this plan and approves the reset approach</li>
                    <li><strong>Execution:</strong> Follow the 11-step recreation sequence (one file at a time)</li>
                    <li><strong>Logging:</strong> Every step must be logged to prompts_log.yaml</li>
                    <li><strong>Verification:</strong> Run the three test cases (Cleanup editing, Compliance audit, Role boundary)</li>
                    <li><strong>Handoff:</strong> When complete, execute /chathandoff to notify other agents of the new setup</li>
                    <li><strong>Monitoring:</strong> Monthly audit of prompts_log.yaml to track ongoing compliance</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

